"{\"uid\": \"worcesternews.co.uk-news-24516646.paris-olympics-star-matt-richards-seen-worcester-pub\", \"text\": \"CelebritiesWorcester  Fresh from the Olympic Games in Paris, gold medallist Matt Richards was spotted enjoying a meal in a village pub.  Richards took photos with staff in The Swan at Martin Hussingtree near\\u00a0Worcester after enjoying a family meal on Saturday evening (August 10).  The Swan's manager, Maisey Prue, revealed she went to school with the 21-year-old Olympian -\\u00a0attending both St Peter's\\u00a0Droitwich and Droitwich Spa\\u00a0High School.  Miss Prue said: \\\"It's brilliant to think that someone I went to school with has achieved something this big.  \\\"He was absolutely lovely too - one of the most down to earth people I have met, and you\\u00a0could ask him anything.\\\"  Richardsreceived a hero's welcomeearlier on Saturday (August 10) as hundreds of neighbours and fans greeted him\\u00a0near his family home in Droitwich.  Miss Prue added: \\\"He was telling us how welcoming everyone had been when he arrived home.  This website and associated newspapers adhere to the Independent Press Standards Organisation's     Editors' Code of Practice. If you have a complaint about the editorial content which relates to     inaccuracy or intrusion, then pleasecontact the editor here.     If you are dissatisfied with the response provided you cancontact IPSO here  \\u00a9 2001-2025. The Worcester Newsis owned and operated by Newsquest Media Group Ltd, an audited local newspaper network.  Visitnewsquest.co.ukto view ourpoliciesandterms.  The Echo Building, 18 Albert Road, Bournemouth, England BH1 1BZ. Registered in England & Wales | 01676637  Data returned from the Piano 'meterActive/meterExpired' callbackevent.  As a subscriber, you are shown80% lessdisplay advertising when reading our                     articles.  Those ads you do see are predominantly fromlocal businessespromotinglocal                         services.  These adverts enabl